<p>This tutorial demonstrates how to set up Remote Desktop access to new Windows instances running in HP Helion OpenStack(R) Since the instances are running full versions of Windows, you must connect to them using Remote Desktop rather than SSH.</p>
<p>The steps needed to do this are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<xref type="section" href="#topic1035/create_security">Create an RDP security group</xref>
</li>
<li>
<xref type="section" href="#topic1035/add_security">Add the RDP security group to the instance</xref>
</li>
<li>
<xref type="section" href="#topic1035/get_pw_cloud">Retrieve the Windows instance password (Public Cloud)</xref>
</li>
<li>
<xref type="section" href="#topic1035/get_pw_hos">Retrieve the Windows instance password (Helion OpenStack(R)</xref>
</li>
</ul>
